author: Harry Lyles Jr.
title: Tyreek Hill pushed away his own teammate to score 95-yard punt return for TD
text:
This return had a little bit everything.
The Kansas City Chiefs were able to extend their lead over the San Diego Chargers on Sunday thanks to another big run by Tyreek Hill.
Hill took a punt back 95 yards as he zoomed by the Chargersâ€™ special teams unit.
Hill even had to evade one of his own teammates from tackling him along the way.
The Chiefs are looking pretty dang good heading into the postseason.
